originalText.text: This shop takes your money and then take advantage of your vehicle. They also take advantage of you if you are a female doing business with them. They had my insurance send the money to one shop and then did the repairs at an Anonymous shop under a different name. My vehicle was vandalized and they informed me that they are not held responsible for any of the damages because it was an a lot with a bunch of other cars. They did not bother to detail the inside of my car once they were done with the repairs that they claim that they have made. When I picked up my car, it looked like it was out for joyrides. They ran my gas down. And they skipped to do a service on my antilock brakes. This company is a scam and a rip off.

originalText.text: Vintage did an amazing job with my car! When I got there I spoke to Jay and he gave me a brief tour of their shop which included a state of the art paint booth that bakes the paint.  The results were flawless! When I picked my car up it looked brand new like nothing was ever damaged!!  The paint job was perfection!! I'm beyond satisfied with my experience at Vintage & recommend anyone who needs work done to go there & ask for Jay for the best service.
